SIMPLE: luxuriate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Luxuriate
<hw>Lux*u"ri*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Luxuriated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Luxuriating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>luxuriatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>luxuriari</ets>, <ets>-are</ets>,
to luxuriate. See <er>Luxury</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To grow exuberantly; to grow to superfluous
abundance.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧ Corn <xex>luxuriates</xex> in a better
mold.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Burton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To feed or live luxuriously; <as>as, the herds
<ex>luxuriate</ex> in the pastures</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To indulge with unrestrained delight and freedom;
<as>as, to <ex>luxuriate</ex> in description</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Luxuriation</ent>⟦br⟧
